{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I draw to better understand things."},{"time":4000,"text":"Sometimes I make a lot of drawings"},{"time":6000,"text":"and I still don't understand what it is I'm drawing."},{"time":9000,"text":"Those of you who are comfortable with digital stuff"},{"time":12000,"text":"and even smug about that relationship might be amused to know"},{"time":16000,"text":"that the guy who is best known for \"The Way Things Work,\""},{"time":19000,"text":"while preparing for part of a panel for called Understanding,"},{"time":24000,"text":"spent two days trying to get his laptop to communicate with his new CD burner."},{"time":33000,"text":"Who knew about extension managers?"},{"time":37000,"text":"I've always managed my own extensions"},{"time":40000,"text":"so it never even occurred to me to read the instructions,"},{"time":43000,"text":"but I did finally figure it out. I had to figure it out,"},{"time":46000,"text":"because along with the invitation"},{"time":49000,"text":"came the frightening reminder that there would be no projector,"},{"time":53000,"text":"so bringing those carousels would no longer be necessary"},{"time":55000,"text":"but some alternate form of communication would."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58000,"text":"Now, I could talk about something that I'm known for,"},{"time":62000,"text":"something that would be particularly appropriate"},{"time":65000,"text":"for many of the more technically minded people here,"},{"time":68000,"text":"or I could talk about something I really care about."},{"time":70000,"text":"I decided to go with the latter."},{"time":73000,"text":"I'm going to talk about Rome."},{"time":74000,"text":"Now, why would I care about Rome, particularly?"},{"time":77000,"text":"Well, I went to Rhode Island School of Design"},{"time":80000,"text":"in the second half of the '60s to study architecture."},{"time":84000,"text":"I was lucky enough to spend my last year, my fifth year,"},{"time":87000,"text":"in Rome as a student. It changed my life."},{"time":91000,"text":"Not the least reason was the fact that I had spent those first four years living at home,"},{"time":96000,"text":"driving into RISD everyday, driving back."},{"time":98000,"text":"I missed the '60s. I read about them; (Laughter)"},{"time":103000,"text":"I understand they were pretty interesting. I missed them,"},{"time":108000,"text":"but I did spend that extraordinary year in Rome,"},{"time":111000,"text":"and it's a place that is never far from my mind."},{"time":115000,"text":"So, whenever given an opportunity,"},{"time":118000,"text":"I try to do something in it or with it or for it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122000,"text":"I also make drawings to help people understand things."},{"time":126000,"text":"Things that I want them to believe I understand."},{"time":128000,"text":"And that's what I do as an illustrator,"},{"time":131000,"text":"that's my job."},{"time":133000,"text":"So, I'm going to show you some pictures of Rome."},{"time":135000,"text":"I've made a lot of drawings of Rome over the years."},{"time":137000,"text":"These are just drawings of Rome. I get back as often as possible --"},{"time":141000,"text":"I need to."},{"time":142000,"text":"All different materials, all different styles, all different times,"},{"time":144000,"text":"drawings from sketchbooks looking at the details of Rome."},{"time":147000,"text":"Part of the reason I'm showing you these"},{"time":150000,"text":"is that it sort of helps illustrate this process I go through"},{"time":153000,"text":"of trying to figure out what it is I feel about Rome and why I feel it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156000,"text":"These are sketches of some of the little details."},{"time":160000,"text":"Rome is a city full of surprises."},{"time":162000,"text":"I mean, we're talking about unusual perspectives,"},{"time":165000,"text":"we're talking about narrow little winding streets"},{"time":167000,"text":"that suddenly open into vast, sun-drenched piazzas --"},{"time":172000,"text":"never, though, piazzas that are not humanly scaled."},{"time":175000,"text":"Part of the reason for that is the fact that they grew up organically."},{"time":178000,"text":"That amazing juxtaposition of old and new,"},{"time":181000,"text":"the bits of light that come down between the buildings"},{"time":187000,"text":"that sort of create a map that's traveling above your head of"},{"time":189000,"text":"usually blue -- especially in the summer --"},{"time":191000,"text":"compared to the map that you would normally expect to see"},{"time":194000,"text":"of conventional streets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196000,"text":"And I began to think about how I could communicate this in book form."},{"time":199000,"text":"How could I share my sense of Rome,"},{"time":202000,"text":"my understanding of Rome?"},{"time":204000,"text":"And I'm going to show you a bunch of dead ends, basically."},{"time":207000,"text":"The primary reason for all these dead ends is when"},{"time":209000,"text":"if you're not quite sure where you're going, you're certainly not going to get there"},{"time":211000,"text":"with any kind of efficiency."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213000,"text":"Here's a little map. And I thought of maps at the beginning;"},{"time":216000,"text":"maybe I should just try and do a little atlas"},{"time":218000,"text":"of my favorite streets and connections in Rome."},{"time":222000,"text":"And here's a line of text that actually evolves"},{"time":226000,"text":"from the exhaust of a scooter zipping across the page."},{"time":228000,"text":"Here that same line of text wraps around a fountain"},{"time":234000,"text":"in an illustration that can be turned upside down and read both ways."},{"time":236000,"text":"Maybe that line of text could be a story"},{"time":239000,"text":"to help give some human aspect to this."},{"time":243000,"text":"Maybe I should get away from this map completely,"},{"time":245000,"text":"and really be honest about wanting to show you my favorite bits and pieces of Rome"},{"time":247000,"text":"and simply kick a soccer ball in the air --"},{"time":249000,"text":"which happens in so many of the squares in the city --"},{"time":251000,"text":"and let it bounce off of things. And I'll simply explain"},{"time":254000,"text":"what each of those things is that the soccer ball hits."},{"time":256000,"text":"That seemed like a sort of a cheap shot."},{"time":258000,"text":"But even though I just started this presentation,"},{"time":262000,"text":"this is not the first thing that I tried to do"},{"time":264000,"text":"and I was getting sort of desperate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265000,"text":"Eventually, I realized that I had really no content that I could count on,"},{"time":268000,"text":"so I decided to move towards packaging. (Laughter)"},{"time":271000,"text":"I mean, it seems to work for a lot of things."},{"time":275000,"text":"So I thought a little box set of four small books might do the trick."},{"time":279000,"text":"But one of the ideas that emerged"},{"time":281000,"text":"from some of those sketches was the notion of traveling through Rome"},{"time":285000,"text":"in different vehicles at different speeds in order"},{"time":288000,"text":"to show the different aspects of Rome."},{"time":292000,"text":"Sort of an overview of Rome and the plan that you might see from a dirigible."},{"time":294000,"text":"Quick snapshots of things you might see"},{"time":298000,"text":"from a speeding motor scooter, and very slow"},{"time":300000,"text":"walking through Rome, you might be able to study in more detail"},{"time":303000,"text":"some of the wonderful surfaces and whatnot that you come across."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310000,"text":"Anyways, I went back to the dirigible notion."},{"time":312000,"text":"Went to Alberto Santos-Dumont."},{"time":315000,"text":"Found one of his dirigibles that had enough dimensions"},{"time":317000,"text":"so I could actually use it as a scale"},{"time":319000,"text":"that I would then juxtapose with some of the things in Rome."},{"time":323000,"text":"This thing would be flying over or past"},{"time":325000,"text":"or be parked in front of, but it would be like having a ruler --"},{"time":327000,"text":"sort of travel through the pages without being a ruler."},{"time":330000,"text":"Not that you know how long number 11 actually is,"},{"time":332000,"text":"but you would be able to compare number 11 against the Pantheon"},{"time":336000,"text":"with number 11 against the Baths of Caracalla,"},{"time":339000,"text":"and so on and so forth. If you were interested."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341000,"text":"This is Beatrix. She has a dog named Ajax,"},{"time":344000,"text":"she has purchased a dirigible -- a small dirigible --"},{"time":347000,"text":"she's assembling the structure,"},{"time":350000,"text":"Ajax is sniffing for holes in the balloon before they set off."},{"time":354000,"text":"She launches this thing above the Spanish Steps"},{"time":357000,"text":"and sets off for an aerial tour of the city."},{"time":360000,"text":"Over the Spanish Steps we go."},{"time":362000,"text":"A nice way to show that river, that stream sort of pouring down the hill."},{"time":366000,"text":"Unfortunately, just across the road from it"},{"time":368000,"text":"or quite close by is the Column of Marcus Aurelius,"},{"time":371000,"text":"and the diameter of the dirigible makes an impression,"},{"time":376000,"text":"as you can see, as she starts trying to read the story that spirals around"},{"time":379000,"text":"the Column of Marcus Aurelius -- gets a little too close, nudges it."},{"time":381000,"text":"This gives me a chance to suggest to you the structure"},{"time":385000,"text":"of the Column of Marcus Aurelius,"},{"time":387000,"text":"which is really no more than a pile of quarters"},{"time":389000,"text":"high -- thick quarters. Over the Piazza of Saint Ignacio,"},{"time":392000,"text":"completely ruining the symmetry, but that aside"},{"time":396000,"text":"a spectacular place to visit."},{"time":400000,"text":"A spectacular framework, inside of which you see, usually,"},{"time":405000,"text":"extraordinary blue sky."},{"time":407000,"text":"Over the Pantheon and the 26-foot diameter Oculus."},{"time":410000,"text":"She parks her dirigible, lowers the anchor rope"},{"time":412000,"text":"and climbs down for a closer look inside."},{"time":416000,"text":"The text here is right side and upside down so that you are forced"},{"time":419000,"text":"to turn the book around, and you can see it from ground point of view"},{"time":422000,"text":"and from her point of view -- looking in the hole,"},{"time":424000,"text":"getting a different kind of perspective,"},{"time":426000,"text":"moving you around the space. Particularly appropriate in a building"},{"time":428000,"text":"that can contain perfectly a sphere"},{"time":432000,"text":"dimensions of the diameter being the same"},{"time":434000,"text":"as the distance from the center of the floor to the center of the Oculus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438000,"text":"Unfortunately for her, the anchor line gets tangled"},{"time":440000,"text":"around the feet of some Boy Scouts who are visiting the Pantheon,"},{"time":442000,"text":"and they are immediately yanked out"},{"time":444000,"text":"and given an extraordinary but terrifying tour"},{"time":447000,"text":"of some of the domes of Rome, which would,"},{"time":450000,"text":"from their point of view, naturally be hanging upside down."},{"time":452000,"text":"They bail out as soon as they get to the top of Saint Ivo,"},{"time":457000,"text":"that little spiral structure you see there."},{"time":459000,"text":"She continues on her way over Piazza Navona."},{"time":463000,"text":"Notices a lot of activity at the Tre Scalini restaurant,"},{"time":465000,"text":"is reminded that it is lunchtime and she's hungry."},{"time":467000,"text":"They keep on motoring towards the Campo de' Fiori,"},{"time":471000,"text":"which they soon reach. Ajax the dog is put in a basket"},{"time":473000,"text":"and lowered with a list of food into the marketplace,"},{"time":476000,"text":"which flourishes there until about one in the afternoon,"},{"time":478000,"text":"and then is completely removed"},{"time":480000,"text":"and doesn't appear again until six or seven the following morning."},{"time":483000,"text":"Anyway, the pooch gets back to the dirigible with the stuff."},{"time":488000,"text":"Unfortunately, when she goes to unwrap the prosciutto,"},{"time":492000,"text":"Ajax makes a lunge for it."},{"time":494000,"text":"She's managed to save the prosciutto,"},{"time":496000,"text":"but in the process she loses the tablecloth,"},{"time":499000,"text":"which you can see flying away in the upper left-hand corner."},{"time":503000,"text":"They continue without their tablecloth,"},{"time":505000,"text":"looking for a place to land this thing so that they can actually have lunch."},{"time":507000,"text":"They eventually discover a huge wall"},{"time":509000,"text":"that's filled with small holes, ideal for docking a dirigible"},{"time":513000,"text":"because you've got a place to tie up."},{"time":515000,"text":"Turns out to be the exterior wall --"},{"time":518000,"text":"that part of it that remains -- of the Coliseum,"},{"time":520000,"text":"so they park themselves there and have a terrific lunch"},{"time":522000,"text":"and have a spectacular view."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523000,"text":"At the end of lunch, they untie the anchor, they set off"},{"time":527000,"text":"through the Baths of Caracalla and over the walls of the city"},{"time":531000,"text":"and then an abandoned gatehouse"},{"time":533000,"text":"and decide to take one more look at the Pyramid of Cestius,"},{"time":537000,"text":"which has this lightning rod on top."},{"time":540000,"text":"Unfortunately, that's a problem: they get a little too close,"},{"time":542000,"text":"and when you're in a dirigible"},{"time":544000,"text":"you have to be very careful about spikes."},{"time":546000,"text":"So that sort of brings her little story to a conclusion."},{"time":549000,"text":"Marcello, on the other hand, is sort of a lazy guy,"},{"time":552000,"text":"but he's not due at work until about noon."},{"time":556000,"text":"So, the alarm goes off and it's five to 12 or so."},{"time":559000,"text":"He gets up, leaps onto his scooter, races through the city"},{"time":562000,"text":"past the church of Santa Maria della Pace,"},{"time":565000,"text":"down the alleys, through the streets"},{"time":568000,"text":"that tourists may be wandering through,"},{"time":570000,"text":"disturbing the quiet backstreet life of Rome at every turn."},{"time":574000,"text":"That speed with which he is moving, I hope I have suggested in this little image,"},{"time":578000,"text":"which, again, can be turned around and read from both sides"},{"time":581000,"text":"because there's text on the bottom and text on the top,"},{"time":585000,"text":"one of which is upside down in this image."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587000,"text":"So, he keeps on moving, approaching an unsuspecting waiter"},{"time":591000,"text":"who is trying to deliver two plates of linguine"},{"time":595000,"text":"in a delicate white wine clam sauce"},{"time":598000,"text":"to diners who are sitting at a table just outside of a restaurant in the street."},{"time":601000,"text":"Waiter catches on, but it's too late."},{"time":603000,"text":"And Marcello keeps moving in his scooter."},{"time":607000,"text":"Everything he sees from this point on is slightly affected by the linguine,"},{"time":611000,"text":"but keeps on moving because this guy's got a job to do."},{"time":613000,"text":"Removes some scaffolding. One of the reasons"},{"time":615000,"text":"Rome remains the extraordinary place it is that"},{"time":618000,"text":"because of scaffolding and the determination"},{"time":621000,"text":"to maintain the fabric, it is a city that continues"},{"time":624000,"text":"to grow and adapt to the needs of the particular time"},{"time":627000,"text":"in which it finds itself, or we find it."},{"time":629000,"text":"Right through the Piazza della Rotonda,"},{"time":632000,"text":"in front of the Pantheon -- again wreaking havoc -- and finally getting to work."},{"time":635000,"text":"Marcello, as it turns out,"},{"time":637000,"text":"is the driver of the number 64 bus,"},{"time":640000,"text":"and if you've been on the number 64 bus, you know"},{"time":642000,"text":"that it's driven with the same kind of exuberance"},{"time":645000,"text":"as Marcello demonstrated on his scooter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648000,"text":"And finally Carletto. You see his apartment in the upper left-hand corner."},{"time":651000,"text":"He's looking at his table;"},{"time":653000,"text":"he's planning to propose this evening to his girlfriend of 40 years, (Laughter)"},{"time":656000,"text":"and he wants it to be perfect."},{"time":660000,"text":"He's got candles out, he's got flowers in the middle"},{"time":663000,"text":"and he's trying to figure out where to put the plates and the glasses."},{"time":665000,"text":"But he's not happy; something's wrong."},{"time":668000,"text":"The phone rings anyway, he's called to the palazzo."},{"time":670000,"text":"He saunters -- he saunters at a good clip,"},{"time":674000,"text":"but as compared to all the traveling we've just seen, he's sauntering."},{"time":676000,"text":"Everybody knows Carletto, because he's in entertainment,"},{"time":679000,"text":"actually; he's in television."},{"time":681000,"text":"He's actually in television repair, which is why people know him."},{"time":686000,"text":"So they all have his number."},{"time":688000,"text":"He arrives at the palazzo, arrives at the big front door."},{"time":691000,"text":"Enters the courtyard and talks to the custodian,"},{"time":694000,"text":"who tells him that there's been a disaster in the palazzo;"},{"time":699000,"text":"nobody's TVs are working"},{"time":701000,"text":"and there's a big soccer game coming up,"},{"time":703000,"text":"and the crowd is getting a little restless and a little nervous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706000,"text":"He goes down to the basement and starts to check the wiring,"},{"time":709000,"text":"and then gradually works his way up to the top of the building,"},{"time":712000,"text":"apartment by apartment, checking every television,"},{"time":714000,"text":"checking every connection,"},{"time":716000,"text":"hoping to find out what this problem is."},{"time":718000,"text":"He works his way up, finally, the grand staircase"},{"time":721000,"text":"and then a smaller staircase until he reaches the attic."},{"time":724000,"text":"He opens the window of the attic, of course, and there's a tablecloth"},{"time":727000,"text":"wrapped around the building's television antenna."},{"time":729000,"text":"He removes it, the problems are solved,"},{"time":731000,"text":"everybody in the palazzo is happy."},{"time":734000,"text":"And of course, he also solves his own problem."},{"time":736000,"text":"All he has to do now, with a perfect table,"},{"time":738000,"text":"is wait for her to arrive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741000,"text":"That was the first attempt, but it didn't seem substantial enough"},{"time":744000,"text":"to convey whatever it was I wanted to convey about Rome."},{"time":748000,"text":"So I thought, well, I'll just do piazzas,"},{"time":751000,"text":"and I'll get inside and underneath"},{"time":753000,"text":"and I'll show these things growing"},{"time":754000,"text":"and show why they're shaped the way they are and so on."},{"time":756000,"text":"And then I thought, that's too complicated. No,"},{"time":758000,"text":"I'll just take my favorite bits and pieces"},{"time":760000,"text":"and I'll put them inside the Pantheon but keep the scale,"},{"time":764000,"text":"so you can see the top of Sant'Ivo and the Pyramid of Cestius"},{"time":766000,"text":"and the Tempietto of Bramante all side by side in this amazing space."},{"time":769000,"text":"Now that's one drawing,"},{"time":773000,"text":"so I thought maybe it's time for Piranesi to meet Escher. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":777000,"text":"You see that I'm beginning to really lose control here"},{"time":780000,"text":"and also hope."},{"time":783000,"text":"There's a very thin blue line of exhaust"},{"time":786000,"text":"that sort of runs through this thing that would be kind of the trail that holds it all together."},{"time":789000,"text":"Then I thought, \"Wait a minute, what am I doing?\""},{"time":790000,"text":"A book is not only a neat way of collecting and storing information,"},{"time":794000,"text":"it's a series of layers."},{"time":796000,"text":"I mean, you always peel one layer off another;"},{"time":799000,"text":"we think of them as pages, doing it a certain way."},{"time":802000,"text":"But think of them as layers. I mean, Rome is a place of layers --"},{"time":806000,"text":"horizontal layers, vertical layers --"},{"time":808000,"text":"and I thought, well just peeling off a page would allow me to --"},{"time":810000,"text":"if I got you thinking about it the right way --"},{"time":813000,"text":"would allow me to sort of show you the depth of layers."},{"time":815000,"text":"The stucco on the walls of most of the buildings in Rome"},{"time":818000,"text":"covers the scars; the scars of centuries of change"},{"time":823000,"text":"as these structures have been adapted"},{"time":826000,"text":"rather than being torn down."},{"time":828000,"text":"If I do a foldout page on the left-hand side"},{"time":832000,"text":"and let you just unfold it, you see behind it what I mean by scar tissue."},{"time":835000,"text":"You can see that in 1635,"},{"time":838000,"text":"it became essential to make smaller windows"},{"time":840000,"text":"because the bad guys were coming or whatever."},{"time":844000,"text":"Adaptations all get buried under the stucco."},{"time":847000,"text":"I could peel out a page of this palazzo to show you what's going on inside of it."},{"time":851000,"text":"But more importantly, I could also show you"},{"time":853000,"text":"what it looks like at the corner of one of those magnificent buildings"},{"time":857000,"text":"with all the massive stone blocks,"},{"time":859000,"text":"or the fake stone blocks done with brick and stucco,"},{"time":862000,"text":"which is more often the case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864000,"text":"So it becomes slightly three-dimensional."},{"time":867000,"text":"I could take you down one of those narrow little streets"},{"time":869000,"text":"into one of those surprising piazzas by using a double gate fold --"},{"time":872000,"text":"double foldout page -- which, if you were like me"},{"time":875000,"text":"reading a pop-up book as a child, you hopefully stick your head into."},{"time":879000,"text":"You wrap the pages around your head"},{"time":881000,"text":"and are in that piazza for that brief period of time."},{"time":884000,"text":"And I've really not done anything much more complicated"},{"time":886000,"text":"than make foldout pages."},{"time":888000,"text":"But then I thought, maybe I could be simpler here."},{"time":890000,"text":"Let's look at the Pantheon and the Piazza della Rotonda in front of it."},{"time":894000,"text":"Here's a book completely wide open."},{"time":896000,"text":"OK, if I don't open the book the whole way,"},{"time":898000,"text":"if I just open it 90 degrees, we're looking down the front of the Pantheon,"},{"time":904000,"text":"and we're looking sort of at the top, more or less down on the square."},{"time":907000,"text":"And if I turn the book the other way,"},{"time":909000,"text":"we're looking across the square at the front of the Pantheon."},{"time":911000,"text":"No foldouts, no tricks --"},{"time":913000,"text":"just a book that isn't open the whole way."},{"time":915000,"text":"That seemed promising. I thought, maybe I'll do it inside"},{"time":917000,"text":"and I can even combine the foldouts with the only partially opened book."},{"time":921000,"text":"So we get inside the Pantheon"},{"time":923000,"text":"and it grows and so on and so forth."},{"time":925000,"text":"And I thought, maybe I'm on the right track,"},{"time":927000,"text":"but it sort of lost its human quality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":929000,"text":"So I went back to the notion of story,"},{"time":931000,"text":"which is always a good thing to have if you're trying to get people"},{"time":933000,"text":"to pay attention to a book and pick up information along the way."},{"time":937000,"text":"\"Pigeon's Progress\" struck me as a catchy title."},{"time":939000,"text":"If it was a homing pigeon,"},{"time":940000,"text":"it would be called \"Homer's Odyssey.\""},{"time":942000,"text":"But it was the journey of the ... (Laughter)"},{"time":944000,"text":"I mean, if a title works, use it. But it would be a journey that went through Rome"},{"time":947000,"text":"and showed all the things that I like about Rome."},{"time":950000,"text":"It's a pigeon sitting on top of a church."},{"time":952000,"text":"Goes off during the day and does normal pigeon stuff. Comes back,"},{"time":954000,"text":"the whole place is covered with scaffolding and green netting"},{"time":957000,"text":"and there's no way this pigeon can get home."},{"time":959000,"text":"So it's a homeless pigeon now"},{"time":962000,"text":"and it's going to have to find another place to live,"},{"time":964000,"text":"and that allows me to go through my catalog of favorite things,"},{"time":966000,"text":"and we start with the tall ones and so on."},{"time":968000,"text":"Maybe it has to go back and live with family members;"},{"time":970000,"text":"that's not always a good thing,"},{"time":972000,"text":"but it does sort of bring pigeons together again."},{"time":975000,"text":"And I thought, that's sort of interesting,"},{"time":977000,"text":"but maybe there's a person who should be involved in this in some way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":980000,"text":"So I kind of came up with this old guy"},{"time":984000,"text":"who spends his life looking after sick pigeons."},{"time":986000,"text":"He'll go anywhere to get them -- dangerous places and whatnot --"},{"time":989000,"text":"and they become really friends with this guy,"},{"time":993000,"text":"and learn to do tricks for him and entertain him at lunchtime and stuff like that."},{"time":996000,"text":"There's a real bond that develops"},{"time":998000,"text":"between this old man and these pigeons."},{"time":1000000,"text":"But unfortunately he gets sick. He gets really sick at the end of the story."},{"time":1004000,"text":"He's taught them to spell his name, which is Aldo."},{"time":1007000,"text":"They show up one day after three or four days of not seeing him --"},{"time":1011000,"text":"he lives in this little garret --"},{"time":1014000,"text":"and they spell his name and fly around."},{"time":1017000,"text":"And he finally gets enough strength together"},{"time":1020000,"text":"to climb up the ladder onto the roof,"},{"time":1023000,"text":"and all the pigeons, a la Red Balloon, are there waiting for him"},{"time":1025000,"text":"and they carry him off over the walls of the city."},{"time":1028000,"text":"And I forgot to mention this:"},{"time":1030000,"text":"whenever he lost a pigeon, he would take that pigeon"},{"time":1032000,"text":"out beyond the walls of the city."},{"time":1034000,"text":"In the old Roman custom, the dead"},{"time":1036000,"text":"were never buried within the walls."},{"time":1038000,"text":"And I thought that's a really cheery story."},{"time":1040000,"text":"(Laughter). That's really going to go a long way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1044000,"text":"So anyway, I went through ... And again, if packaging doesn't work"},{"time":1047000,"text":"and if the stories aren't going anywhere,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"I just come up with titles"},{"time":1051000,"text":"and hope that a title will sort of kick me off in the right direction."},{"time":1054000,"text":"And sometimes it does focus me enough"},{"time":1056000,"text":"and I'll even do a title page."},{"time":1060000,"text":"So, these are all title pages that eventually led me"},{"time":1063000,"text":"to the solution I settled on, which is the story of a young woman"},{"time":1066000,"text":"who sends a message on a homing pigeon --"},{"time":1069000,"text":"she lives outside the walls of the city of Rome -- to someone in the city."},{"time":1071000,"text":"And the pigeon is flying down above the Appian Way here."},{"time":1075000,"text":"You can see the tombs and pines and so on and so forth along the way."},{"time":1079000,"text":"If you see the red line,"},{"time":1080000,"text":"you are seeing the trail of the pigeon;"},{"time":1081000,"text":"if you don't see the red line, you are the pigeon."},{"time":1084000,"text":"And it becomes necessary and possible, at this point,"},{"time":1087000,"text":"to try to convey what that sense would be like"},{"time":1090000,"text":"of flying over the city without actually moving."},{"time":1092000,"text":"Past the Pyramid of Cestius --"},{"time":1095000,"text":"these will seem very familiar to you, even if you haven't been to Rome recently --"},{"time":1099000,"text":"past the gatehouse."},{"time":1101000,"text":"This is something that's a little bit unusual."},{"time":1103000,"text":"This pigeon does something that most homing pigeons do not do:"},{"time":1106000,"text":"it takes the scenic route, (Laughter) which was a device"},{"time":1108000,"text":"that I felt was necessary to actually extend this book"},{"time":1111000,"text":"beyond about four pages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1113000,"text":"So, we circle around the Coliseum, past the Church of Santa Maria in Cosmedin"},{"time":1119000,"text":"and the Temple of Hercules towards the river."},{"time":1123000,"text":"We almost collide with the cornice of the Palazzo Farnese --"},{"time":1126000,"text":"designed by Michelangelo,"},{"time":1129000,"text":"built of stone taken from the Coliseum -- narrow escape."},{"time":1132000,"text":"We swoop down over the Campo de' Fiori."},{"time":1136000,"text":"This is one of those things I show to my students"},{"time":1138000,"text":"because it's a complete bastardization --"},{"time":1140000,"text":"a denial of any rules of perspective."},{"time":1144000,"text":"The only rule of perspective that I think matters is"},{"time":1146000,"text":"if it looks believable, you've succeeded."},{"time":1149000,"text":"But you try and figure out where the vanishing points meet here;"},{"time":1151000,"text":"a couple are on Mars and"},{"time":1153000,"text":"a couple of others in Cremona."},{"time":1156000,"text":"But into the piazza in front of Santa Maria della Pace,"},{"time":1159000,"text":"where invariably a soccer game is going on,"},{"time":1161000,"text":"and we're hit by a soccer ball."},{"time":1163000,"text":"Now this is a terrible illustration of being hit by a soccer ball."},{"time":1166000,"text":"I have all the pieces:"},{"time":1168000,"text":"there's Santa Maria della Pace, there's a soccer ball,"},{"time":1170000,"text":"there's a little bit of a bird's wing -- nothing's happening,"},{"time":1172000,"text":"so I had to rethink it."},{"time":1176000,"text":"And if you do want to see Santa Maria della Pace,"},{"time":1179000,"text":"these books are really flexible, incredibly interactive --"},{"time":1181000,"text":"just turn it around and look at it the other way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1183000,"text":"Through the alley, we can see the impact is captured in the red line."},{"time":1187000,"text":"And then bird manages to pull itself together past this medieval tower --"},{"time":1193000,"text":"one of the few remaining medieval towers --"},{"time":1197000,"text":"towards the church of Sant'Agnese"},{"time":1200000,"text":"and around the dome looking down into Piazza Navona --"},{"time":1202000,"text":"which we've already mentioned and seen and flown over a couple of times;"},{"time":1205000,"text":"there's the Bernini statue of the Four Rivers --"},{"time":1209000,"text":"and then past the wonderful Borromini Sant'Ivo,"},{"time":1214000,"text":"stopping just long enough on the 26-foot diameter Oculus"},{"time":1217000,"text":"of the Pantheon to catch our breath."},{"time":1219000,"text":"And then we can swoop inside and around; and because we're flying,"},{"time":1221000,"text":"we don't really have to worry about gravity at this particular moment in time,"},{"time":1223000,"text":"so this drawing can be oriented in any way on the page."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1228000,"text":"We get a little exuberant as we pass Gesu;"},{"time":1232000,"text":"it's not surprising to sort of mimic the architecture in this way."},{"time":1235000,"text":"Past the wonderful wall filled with the juxtaposition that I was talking about;"},{"time":1240000,"text":"beautiful carvings set into the walls above the neon \"Ristorante\" sign, and so on."},{"time":1244000,"text":"And eventually, we arrive at the courtyard of the palazzo,"},{"time":1246000,"text":"which is our destination."},{"time":1248000,"text":"Straight up through the courtyard"},{"time":1250000,"text":"into a little window into the attic,"},{"time":1253000,"text":"where somebody is working at the drawing board."},{"time":1256000,"text":"He removes the message from the leg of the bird; this is what it says."},{"time":1258000,"text":"As we look at the drawing board,"},{"time":1261000,"text":"we see what he's working on is, in fact,"},{"time":1263000,"text":"a map of the journey that the pigeon has just taken,"},{"time":1265000,"text":"and the red line extends through all the sights."},{"time":1267000,"text":"And if you want the information, so that we complete this cycle of understanding,"},{"time":1270000,"text":"all you have to do is read these paragraphs."},{"time":1273000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}